===Nominal Phrase===
'''penalty box''' (''plural'' '''penalty boxes''')
#{{icehockey}} An enclosed bench where a player must remain for timed period (a [[penalty]]) that is assessed after an infraction
#:''Both players got to cool their heels for five minutes in their respective '''penalty boxes''' after the fight.''

[[Category:Nominal phrases]]
minor penalties are for 2 minutes and major penalties are for 4 minutes in the penalty box.  A variety of time-based penalties can be assessed as well, but players typically serve only 2 & 4 minutes in the box.

